# Shared String Codecs

If the backend contract forces multiple logical fields into one string, treat that string as a codec boundary, not ad hoc text manipulation.

## Required Rules

- Create one shared encoder and one shared decoder near the service layer.
- UI components and mutation hooks must call the shared codec helpers instead of building packed strings inline.
- Decoding must be backward-compatible with existing stored values.
- User-entered delimiters must round-trip safely. If a legacy delimiter format must stay, parse from known boundaries and preserve the middle text.
- Prefer first-class API fields over packed strings whenever the API supports them.

## Required Coverage

- Round-trip plain text values
- Round-trip values containing the delimiter
- Decode legacy values with missing or partial segments
- Preserve priority/metadata after refresh

## Anti-Patterns

- Inline templates like `` `${icon}|${text}|${priority}` ``
- Raw `split('|')` parsing in multiple files
- Separate encoding rules for create vs update vs move operations
